📚 أهمية "Study with me" 📚

نظام "Study with me" يوفر بيئة تفاعلية ومحفزة للدراسة. من خلال الانضمام لجلسات دراسية مشتركة، يمكنك:

تعزيز التركيز: البيئة المشتركة تساعد على تقليل التشتت وزيادة الإنتاجية.
تحفيز الإلهام: رؤية الآخرين يعملون يمكن أن تكون دافعًا قويًا لمواصلة المذاكرة.
بناء الروتين: الالتزام بمواعيد محددة للدراسة يساهم في تنظيم الوقت.
الدعم المتبادل: مشاركة التحديات والنصائح مع زملائك تساعد على تخطي العقبات.
📖 بنذاكر بتقنية بومودورو 50/10! 📖

تعتبر تقنية بومودورو 50/10 من أفضل الطرق لتحسين إنتاجيتك في الدراسة. تعتمد على:

50 دقيقة تركيز: خصص 50 دقيقة للدراسة بتركيز تام. اجعل هذه الفترة خالية من المشتتات.
10 دقائق استراحة: بعد كل 50 دقيقة، خذ 10 دقائق للاسترخاء. يمكنك القيام بتمارين بسيطة أو شرب كوب من الماء.
لماذا تعمل هذه الطريقة؟

زيادة الإنتاجية: يساعد التناوب بين التركيز والاستراحة في تعزيز القدرة على التحصيل.
تجنب الإرهاق: الاستراحات القصيرة تمنحك الطاقة للاستمرار.
تحسين التركيز: فترات العمل الطويلة تجعل عقلك أكثر استجابة واستعدادًا للتعلم.
جرب تقنية بومودورو 50/10 اليوم وراقب كيف ستتحسن نتائجك! 🌟

📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

S23.description:
この放送は 【１】日本初の勉強動画を24時間毎日放送 【２】YouTubeLiveを活用したオンライン自習室 【３】学習記録機能付きのチャット です。(最新のお知らせ: https://www.notion.so/manten120/1e3702349dcc4cdea53fcfc812d89ff9?pvs=4)

【１】

日本初！24時間毎日、勉強している姿を放送し続けるチャンネルです。

This is Japanese First 24/7/365 study broad cast

生放送と再放送を交互に行い24時間放送しています(2018年8月14日開始)

★10年間、毎日生放送します　※2028年まで。生放送の時間帯は主のライフスタイルの変化に応じて変わります。

★右下のタイマーは

⏰25分勉強(赤)

⏰5分休憩(緑)

を繰り返しています

4回目の休憩は20分です

🍅このタイマーによる勉強法をポモドーロ勉強法といいます🍅

🍅この放送では25分間の勉強を1回することを "1コマ勉強する" と数えています🍅

【２】

日本で初めてYouTubeLiveを活用したオンライン自習室(通称：満点ルーム)です！

配信主Mantenが運営するオンライン自習室(満点ルーム)で視聴者さんどうし一緒に勉強しませんか? 

スマホやウェブカメラで机をうつせば、あなたの部屋が世界中の人と一緒に勉強できる自習室になります。

たまにYouTubeにうつります。

満点ルームの運営管理は全て かずちゃむ (Twitter: https://twitter.com/kazchamu_manten ) ちゃんにお任せしております

満点ルームの使い方  https://manten120.notion.site/c31bd3cef255412da64be11334516d8d?pvs=4

【３】

世界初!! YoutubeLiveのチャットで学習の記録をつけられます！

コマンド(!25など)をチャットに書き込むことで学習記録をつけることができます。

満点学習帳 ( https://www.mantenroom.com ) と連携しています。

くわしくは上記リンクと下の 【コマンドの使い方】 にて。

【コマンドの使い方】

!25 など!で始まる単語をコマンドと言います。コマンドをチャットに書き込むとbot(自動返信ロボット🤖)を通じて学習の記録をつけられます。

!make

あなたの学習記録ページを作成します

学習記録ページはサイト満点学習帳 ( https://www.mantenroom.com )  に作成されます。

!home

あなたの学習記録ページのURLを返します

!25

1回25分の勉強回数(コマ数)を記録します

今日のコマ数と過去全期間の累計コマ数を返します

学習記録ページに反映されます

(!25aと!25bも同じ機能のコマンドです

ほかの人とタイミングがかぶると反応しないので、

かぶりやすいこのコマンドだけ3種類用意してます)

!delete

学習記録ページに関するすべてのデータを削除します😭

そのほか満点学習帳と連携するコマンドの一覧は『学習記録ページ → ? → 目標設定(仮) → ページ最下部』にて見れます。

ここまでのコマンドは主にコマルチャンbotが返信してくれます⛄

コマルチャンbotが担当するのは満点学習帳・学習記録・満点ルームに関するコマンドです。

満点ルームに関するコマンドは

!room

📌 Background - Real ASMR sounds (🌧️ Rain, ⛈️ Thunder, 🔥 Fire Crackling, 🌿 Nature Sounds).

🤖 !start – Start your study session.
🤖 !target "your goal" – Set your study goal. Example: !target 2 chapters
🤖 !done "your goal" – Mark it done when you finish. Example: !done 2 chapters
🤖 !break – Take a break when needed.
🤖 !points – Track your study hours & points. 🏆

S67.title: LIVE | Study with me | 3 Hrs | Focus 2025-05-15 12:35
S67.description:
Welcome to my “Study With Me” 2-hour live study session! Whether you’re preparing for an exam, working on an assignment, or just trying to stay productive, this video is designed to help you stay focused, motivated, and accountable. Join me as I study live for 2 hours straight, no distractions, just pure study time — and feel like you’re studying with a friend, right from the comfort of your home!

This is a real-time study session (recorded live) where we study together for 2 hours continuously. It’s perfect for those who enjoy the Pomodoro technique, body doubling, or need a virtual study buddy to stay on track. Whether you’re a student preparing for your school, college, university exams, competitive exams like NEET, JEE, UPSC, SAT, GRE, GMAT, or simply working on a personal project, this video will give you the environment you need to stay committed.

In this video:
✅ 2 hours of live study
✅ Minimal talking for maximum focus
✅ Realistic study atmosphere: no music, no distractions, just natural sounds
✅ Perfect for “study with me” fans, deep work sessions, and productivity seekers

WHY WATCH THIS STUDY WITH ME VIDEO?

I created this study with me live stream to help fellow students stay motivated and create a sense of companionship even while studying alone. Sometimes we all need someone by our side, even virtually, to keep going. This video can help boost your productivity, especially if you’re struggling with procrastination or want a structured block of study time.

Feel free to pause, replay, or study alongside me in real-time. You can even use this as a timer or background video while you tackle your own work.

S81.description:
🧉 Hello student, how are you? It's great to have you here!
I just wanted to let you know that this study livestream is live 24 hours a day, every day of the week, so that whenever you feel like studying, you can rely on a platform that motivates you and enables you to achieve that goal. And if you ever feel like appearing on the livestream, join us on this Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]

💰💸Crowdfunding to buy a camera for the channel (since the cell phone I use as a camera is starting to give problems): https://livepix.gg/vaquinha/comprar-camera

But before we begin, if possible, please leave a like on the video, subscribe to the channel, and share your study objectives in the comments!
Finally, grab your water, matecito, coffee, or tea to stay hydrated during your study sessions.

👾 Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]
(To join the video call, go to the category "----- 🔴 live stream -----" and then to the channel "🔴-live-🔴")

📅 Schedule for the next livestream: [https://www.canva.com/design/DAE9uFPN...]

🍅 Pomodoro Technique:
We will be using the Pomodoro technique, which consists of four 50-minute study sessions, interspersed with 10-minute breaks. The purpose of this technique is to maintain focus for 50 minutes through conditioning. In the beginning, it might be difficult, so try starting with cycles of 15-25 minutes. However, with persistence, you can achieve the desired results!

⭐ A little bit about me and why I created this channel:
My name is Arthur, I'm 24 years old, and I'm a third-year medical student at UBA College. I created this channel to help myself maintain discipline and focus in my studies, and if possible, to also help other students do the same.
Instagram channel: @so_50_minutos

S95.description:
🎓✨ Struggling to concentrate while studying?
Do you get easily distracted, lose track of time, and end up frustrated because you didn’t make progress?
Are you preparing for an important exam and feeling anxious, mentally drained, or unsure of where to start?
Do you compare yourself to others and doubt yourself, even though you’re giving your best effort?
Do you study alone and feel like you’re missing structure, accountability, or someone to keep you on track?

💬 If any of this sounds like you, this channel is for you.

🎥 Welcome to your new study and focus sanctuary.
I’m a Latina doctor living in the Netherlands, and here I share my real study sessions as I review medicine in Spanish, English, and Dutch. I also share the tools, habits, and strategies that have helped me successfully complete two university degrees, learn languages, and stay motivated even on tough days.

🧠 This channel is designed to help you study better, with more focus, and without feeling alone in your journey.

✨ What will you find here?
📚 Study With Me live sessions using the Pomodoro Technique to stay focused
💡 Practical study tips based on real-life experience
🎥 Videos to beat procrastination and study strategically
🌧️ Rain sounds, ASMR, lofi music, and calming environments that enhance concentration
🤝 A real community that motivates, supports, and helps you make steady progress without toxic pressure

📲 Subscribe and activate 🔔 notifications to transform your study routine.
💬 Join our virtual study community, where we motivate, hold each other accountable, and grow together — step by step, without perfection, but with purpose.
🎓✨ ¿Te cuesta concentrarte cuando estudias?
¿Te distraes fácilmente, el tiempo se va volando y terminas frustrado/a porque no avanzas?
¿Estás preparando un examen importante y sientes ansiedad, agotamiento mental o no sabes por dónde empezar?
¿Te comparas con otros estudiantes, dudas de ti mismo/a y pierdes la motivación aunque estés haciendo tu mayor esfuerzo?
¿Estudias solo/a y te falta estructura, constancia o alguien que te acompañe en el proceso?

💬 Si respondiste “sí” a alguna de estas preguntas, este canal es para ti.

🎥 Bienvenido/a a tu nuevo santuario de estudio y enfoque.
Soy médica latina viviendo en los Países Bajos, y aquí comparto mis sesiones reales de estudio mientras repaso medicina en español, inglés y neerlandés. Además, te enseño las herramientas, hábitos y estrategias que me han permitido estudiar dos carreras universitarias, aprender idiomas y mantener la motivación incluso en los días difíciles.

🧠 Este canal está diseñado para ayudarte a estudiar mejor, con más enfoque y sin sentirte solo/a.

✨ ¿Qué encontrarás aquí?
📚 Estudia Conmigo en vivo con técnica Pomodoro para mantener el foco
💡 Tips prácticos de estudio basados en experiencia real
🎥 Videos para vencer la procrastinación y estudiar con estrategia
🌧️ Sonidos de lluvia, ASMR, música lofi y ambientes relajantes que activan tu concentración
🤝 Una comunidad real que te motiva, te acompaña y te ayuda a avanzar sin presión tóxica

📲 Suscríbete y activa 🔔 las notificaciones para transformar tu rutina de estudio.
💬 Únete a nuestra comunidad de estudio virtual donde nos motivamos, rendimos cuentas y progresamos juntos — paso a paso, sin perfección, pero con propósito.

S97.title: Study with me Live |For UPSC CSE | Pomodoro Method | Interaction in Break | Study Stream |Exam Prep 2025-05-15 12:36
S97.description:
Welcome to "Study with me" sessions 📚

About me : 

Currently Preparing for UPSC CSE 2025 

Graduated from University of Allahaabad . 

We'll use the Pomodoro method for studying :

50 min study 
10 min break
and after every 2 session 
Long break of 20 minutes
 Target will to complete 9 Sessions 😊😊
❗️ Rules ❗️
Use English in the livestream chat so the moderators can make sure everyone is safe. Some brief messages in different languages are okay, but not full conversations.
No spam (text or emojis)
Keep chatting to a minimum in study time
Keep using all caps to a minimum
Be nice and polite and inclusive of all! 😊
Respect mine and the moderators decisions (this includes warnings, time-outs and bans ).

Join telegram for schedule and stream related information-  https://t.me/+iBQZi2lddKM5YjNl


💬 COMMANDS
[Task Bot]
!a my-task: add my-task to list
!n next-task: finish the existing task and add next-task to list
!f: finish the existing task
!e edited-task: edit the existing task to edited-task
!r: remove the existing task
